255
00:37:42,170 --> 00:37:44,079
Hey, pal. I got a delivery on five.

256
00:37:45,005 --> 00:37:46,500
I don't think there's anybody up there.

257
00:37:46,590 --> 00:37:51,050
Oh, man. I'm gonna catch hell
if I don't collect. You got to let me try.

258
00:37:52,969 --> 00:37:56,585
I'll tell you what. I got an extra medium.
Take it on the house.

259
00:38:03,476 --> 00:38:06,594
- You are the man.
- God bless you, brother.

260
00:38:09,146 --> 00:38:10,260
All right.

261
00:38:25,574 --> 00:38:27,364
(COMPUTERS BLEEPING)

262
00:39:07,978 --> 00:39:09,092
Okay.

263
00:40:22,612 --> 00:40:24,983
We're pretty well closed here, folks.
I'm sorry.

264
00:40:25,072 --> 00:40:27,478
Oh, come on, Stan. It's Friday night.

265
00:40:28,657 --> 00:40:30,364
Oh, kids.

266
00:40:30,782 --> 00:40:33,025
I got nothing but marinara now.

267
00:40:33,119 --> 00:40:35,157
Oh, I got to have a Mister Pink, please.

268
00:40:35,244 --> 00:40:37,451
She worked through dinner again,
of course.

269
00:40:45,168 --> 00:40:46,282
Stan?

270
00:40:47,711 --> 00:40:52,039
And he... I go, " So, yeah,
I mean, where were you?

271
00:40:52,132 --> 00:40:54,170
"I can't... I don't know
where you were, Cecil."

272
00:40:54,257 --> 00:40:56,748
And he goes, "Not where you been at."

273
00:40:56,842 --> 00:41:00,543
I thought, "Oh, my God." I just felt so awful.

274
00:41:25,487 --> 00:41:27,146
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

275
00:41:28,114 --> 00:41:29,523
Bruce?

276
00:41:36,119 --> 00:41:39,155
Betty? What's going on?

277
00:41:54,507 --> 00:41:55,621
Betty...

278
00:41:55,715 --> 00:41:58,798
Just tell me if I saw what I think I saw.

279
00:42:00,094 --> 00:42:03,793
- I don't know what to say.
- Please, just tell me the truth.

280
00:42:45,166 --> 00:42:47,786
BETTY: Don't go. Don't go.

281
00:42:57,632 --> 00:42:59,588
I want you to come with me now.

282
00:42:59,675 --> 00:43:01,882
Please. Come with me.

283
00:43:03,302 --> 00:43:04,547
Please.

284
00:43:34,657 --> 00:43:36,199
BETTY: It's our data.

285
00:43:37,159 --> 00:43:40,159
I got in there before they carted it all away.

286
00:43:42,413 --> 00:43:46,077
I hoped somewhere that it might tell us
something someday.

287
00:43:48,416 --> 00:43:53,077
- Does the General know that you have this?
- No, I don't think so.

288
00:43:53,170 --> 00:43:55,494
I haven't spoken to him in a couple of years.

289
00:43:55,588 --> 00:43:57,083
You have to be sure.

290
00:43:57,172 --> 00:44:02,213
Bruce, I don't understand why we can't
just go in there together and talk to him.

291
00:44:02,302 --> 00:44:07,257
He told me what he wanted to do.
He wants it out of me.

292
00:44:07,346 --> 00:44:10,594
He wants to dissect it
so that he can replicate it.

293
00:44:10,681 --> 00:44:12,840
He wants to make it a weapon.

294
00:45:04,800 --> 00:45:06,081
- Hi.
- Hi.

295
00:45:07,219 --> 00:45:11,132
- I thought you might want to...
- Thanks.

296
00:45:13,014 --> 00:45:16,597
Listen, I should leave early,
as early as I can.

297
00:45:16,684 --> 00:45:20,099
Really? You can't stay at all?

298
00:45:20,186 --> 00:45:23,518
I want to,
but it's just not safe for me to be here.

299
00:45:26,065 --> 00:45:28,815
- lf I could borrow some cash...
- Of course.

300
00:45:28,900 --> 00:45:30,525
I need to take a bus.

301
00:45:30,610 --> 00:45:33,313
Well, at least let me walk you to the station.

302
00:45:35,280 --> 00:45:36,393
Okay.

303
00:45:40,240 --> 00:45:42,731
- You have everything you need?
- Yeah.

304
00:45:45,913 --> 00:45:46,992
I...

305
00:45:48,414 --> 00:45:49,494
What?

306
00:45:51,875 --> 00:45:53,951
- Good night.
- Good night.

307
00:45:54,043 --> 00:45:56,034
I hope you get some rest.

308
00:46:38,155 --> 00:46:40,775
We're giving you a very low dose only.

309
00:46:41,114 --> 00:46:43,784
I need you sharp out there and disciplined.

310
00:46:43,867 --> 00:46:45,858
First sign of any side effect,

311
00:46:45,952 --> 00:46:49,617
we stop and you're off team
until you straighten out.

312
00:46:50,414 --> 00:46:52,157
- Agreed?
- Agreed.

313
00:46:56,085 --> 00:46:58,835
You'll get two separate infusions.

314
00:46:58,920 --> 00:47:03,130
One into the deep muscle,
one into the bone marrow centres.

315
00:47:03,213 --> 00:47:05,503
The bone ones are going to hurt.

316
00:47:20,518 --> 00:47:21,762
(GRUNTS)

317
00:47:52,121 --> 00:47:53,864
Is everything okay?

318
00:47:55,833 --> 00:47:57,208
I think so.

319
00:47:58,460 --> 00:48:00,166
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

320
00:48:05,590 --> 00:48:06,918
Come here.

321
00:48:08,592 --> 00:48:10,630
- I just wanna do this.
- Oh.

322
00:48:11,844 --> 00:48:13,882
- It's better like that.
- Yeah?

323
00:48:18,681 --> 00:48:20,175
It feels too tight, huh?

324
00:48:20,266 --> 00:48:22,056
- Yeah, a little.
- Okay.

325
00:48:29,521 --> 00:48:32,521
- What?
- They're here.

326
00:48:32,856 --> 00:48:34,268
- Betty, look at me, look at me!
- Bruce!

327
00:48:34,358 --> 00:48:35,603
You have to go far away
from me as you can!

328
00:48:35,693 --> 00:48:37,186
- Don't argue with me, just go. Go!
- Bruce!

329
00:48:42,614 --> 00:48:44,405
(CAR ALARM SOUNDING)

330
00:48:48,367 --> 00:48:50,489
Damn it! We'd have had snipers on target
in three more minutes.

331
00:48:50,577 --> 00:48:52,119
I wanna know who jumped the gun.

332
00:48:54,373 --> 00:48:55,570
He's heading 2 -7 -0 .

333
00:49:12,717 --> 00:49:14,378
Blonsky! Not yet!

334
00:49:15,844 --> 00:49:17,007
Sir.

335
00:49:18,639 --> 00:49:20,262
Look alive. This could get interesting.

336
00:50:08,255 --> 00:50:09,333
I got him!

337
00:50:09,630 --> 00:50:12,715
Stop! Stop!

338
00:50:14,552 --> 00:50:15,925
I know you're in there!

339
00:50:17,762 --> 00:50:19,385
General, please!

340
00:50:21,889 --> 00:50:22,920
Sir?

341
00:50:23,556 --> 00:50:24,635
Dad!

342
00:50:32,105 --> 00:50:36,231
- Dad, please don't do this.
- You can't see this clearly. Now, get inside.

343
00:50:36,315 --> 00:50:38,141
There he is!

344
00:50:38,233 --> 00:50:40,438
<i>SOLDIER 1 ON RADIO:</i>
<i>Target is in the overpass. We have a visual.</i>

345
00:50:40,525 --> 00:50:42,684
Do not engage! Repeat, do not engage!

346
00:50:48,407 --> 00:50:49,949
SOLDIER 2 : He's locked in.

347
00:50:55,954 --> 00:50:57,494
Put two canisters in there with him.

348
00:50:58,121 --> 00:50:59,237
SOLDIER: Fire!

349
00:51:18,344 --> 00:51:19,505
Get her back here!

350
00:51:40,317 --> 00:51:41,644
(GRUNTING)

351
00:51:53,992 --> 00:51:55,023
Now she'll see.

352
00:51:55,994 --> 00:51:57,192
(ROARING)

353
00:52:03,458 --> 00:52:04,786
(GROWLING)

354
00:52:11,380 --> 00:52:12,873
(ROARING)

355
00:52:17,884 --> 00:52:18,998
Alpha team?

356
00:52:21,010 --> 00:52:22,090
Let him have all of it.

357
00:52:28,349 --> 00:52:29,842
SOLDIER 2 : Come on, light him up!

358
00:52:33,101 --> 00:52:36,434
Where are the fifty cals? Move your asses!

359
00:53:03,706 --> 00:53:05,034
(GRUNTING)

360
00:53:24,596 --> 00:53:25,793
Oh, my God!

361
00:53:29,432 --> 00:53:30,463
Blonsky, now you're up!

362
00:53:31,184 --> 00:53:32,297
Sir?

363
00:53:33,476 --> 00:53:34,757
Cover me.

364
00:53:51,697 --> 00:53:52,775
(GROWLING)

365
00:53:52,864 --> 00:53:54,358
Remember me?

366
00:54:14,338 --> 00:54:15,711
My God, he's doing it.

367
00:54:20,759 --> 00:54:22,085
Move him toward the cannons!

368
00:54:28,221 --> 00:54:29,300
SOLDIER: Move!

369
00:54:35,893 --> 00:54:37,090
(GROWLS)

370
00:54:42,815 --> 00:54:44,059
Hold your position!

371
00:54:44,148 --> 00:54:45,476
BLONSKY: Do it now!

372
00:54:47,150 --> 00:54:49,023
(HIGH-PITCHED BUZZING)

373
00:54:53,405 --> 00:54:54,731
(GRUNTING)

374
00:55:11,335 --> 00:55:12,876
Please, please, please, no!

375
00:55:12,960 --> 00:55:14,369
- Please, please, please!
- Get her back!

376
00:55:14,460 --> 00:55:15,492
You're killing him!

377
00:55:15,586 --> 00:55:17,911
BETTY: Stop! Get off of me!

378
00:55:22,278 --> 00:55:26,135
Bruce! Bruce!

379
00:55:55,530 --> 00:55:56,572
Where's the gunship?

380
00:56:16,795 --> 00:56:17,838
Is that it?

381
00:56:18,045 --> 00:56:19,817
Blonsky, pull back now.

382
00:56:19,922 --> 00:56:21,172
<i>Pull back!</i>

383
00:56:24,300 --> 00:56:26,072
Is that all you got?

384
00:56:26,697 --> 00:56:27,739
(GROWLS)

385
00:56:33,681 --> 00:56:36,286
- Fall back!
- SOLDIER 3 : Fall back! Let's go, let's go!

386
00:56:36,391 --> 00:56:37,746
GENERAL: Find cover!

387
00:56:41,706 --> 00:56:42,958
Betty!

388
00:56:56,403 --> 00:56:57,864
Fire, goddamn it!

389
00:56:59,739 --> 00:57:00,885
Bruce?

390
00:57:00,990 --> 00:57:02,867
(HELICOPTER APPROACHING)

391
00:57:14,125 --> 00:57:15,271
Stop firing!

392
00:57:28,822 --> 00:57:30,282
No!

393
00:57:59,885 --> 00:58:01,135
(GROWLS)

394
00:58:20,418 --> 00:58:22,922
You did the right thing, calling us.

395
00:58:25,005 --> 00:58:27,925
I need to know where they're going.

396
00:58:28,028 --> 00:58:30,217
She'll be in incredible danger
as long as she's with him.

397
00:58:30,322 --> 00:58:31,572
From who?

398
00:58:32,510 --> 00:58:35,117
He protected her. You almost killed her.

399
00:58:35,222 --> 00:58:38,869
I give you my word, her safety
is my main concern at this point.

400
00:58:38,972 --> 00:58:41,682
You know, it's a point
of professional pride with me

401
00:58:41,788 --> 00:58:44,706
that I can always tell
when somebody's lying.

402
00:58:45,019 --> 00:58:46,166
And you are.

403
00:58:47,416 --> 00:58:49,710
I don't know where he's going.

404
00:58:50,648 --> 00:58:54,818
- I know she'll help him, if she can.
- Then she's aiding a fugitive.

405
00:58:56,068 --> 00:58:58,673
And I can't help either one of them.

406
00:59:03,677 --> 00:59:06,804
I used to wonder
why she never talked about you.

407
00:59:07,117 --> 00:59:08,576
Now I know!

408
00:59:13,476 --> 00:59:15,768
GENERAL: Where does she meet these guys?

409
00:59:54,545 --> 00:59:55,900
(SCREAMING)

410
00:59:56,838 --> 00:59:57,985
(GROANS)

411
01:00:05,280 --> 01:00:06,427
Bruce?

412
01:00:16,643 --> 01:00:17,789
Bruce.

413
01:00:26,130 --> 01:00:27,275
(ROARING)

414
01:00:38,012 --> 01:00:40,201
It's okay. It's okay.

415
01:00:53,335 --> 01:00:56,045
Come here. Come this way.

416
01:00:59,275 --> 01:01:00,838
Watch your head.

417
01:01:15,952 --> 01:01:17,099
Okay.

418
01:01:27,942 --> 01:01:29,088
We're okay.

419
01:01:33,987 --> 01:01:35,342
It's okay.

420
01:01:37,217 --> 01:01:38,885
It's just the rain.

421
01:01:48,163 --> 01:01:50,353
GENERAL: Will he ever walk again?

422
01:01:50,456 --> 01:01:54,000
DOCTOR: Most of the bones in his body
look like crushed gravel right now.

423
01:01:54,103 --> 01:01:57,960
I will say this for him.
He's got a heart like a machine.

424
01:01:58,065 --> 01:02:01,192
Never seen anything like it,
outside of a racehorse.

425
01:03:03,735 --> 01:03:04,880
Here.

426
01:03:06,445 --> 01:03:07,590
Okay.

427
01:03:19,579 --> 01:03:20,724
(GASPS)

428
01:03:29,793 --> 01:03:31,045
(PANTING)

429
01:03:33,338 --> 01:03:34,902
(BRUCE VOMITING)

430
01:03:48,244 --> 01:03:49,494
Bruce?

431
01:03:50,954 --> 01:03:52,204
Oh, hi.

432
01:03:52,829 --> 01:03:53,873
Are you okay?

433
01:03:54,601 --> 01:03:55,644
Yeah.

434
01:03:55,853 --> 01:03:58,146
Yeah, actually, I feel a lot better.

435
01:03:58,250 --> 01:04:00,751
- Good.
- I just had to get my data back.

436
01:04:02,315 --> 01:04:03,461
You ate it?

437
01:04:03,565 --> 01:04:07,840
Well, you know, the circumstances
called for a little improvisation.

438
01:04:07,943 --> 01:04:08,987
Wow.

439
01:04:10,445 --> 01:04:14,822
Okay, so they didn't have a great selection,
but I got you some options.

440
01:04:14,927 --> 01:04:17,429
First thing's first.

441
01:04:17,534 --> 01:04:19,202
Oh, you're kidding me.

442
01:04:29,418 --> 01:04:30,565
What?

443
01:04:31,190 --> 01:04:34,003
- No.
- They were the stretchiest pair they had.

444
01:04:34,108 --> 01:04:35,358
I'll take my chances.

445
01:04:35,672 --> 01:04:38,068
<i>FEMALE REPORTER: Rumours continue</i>
<i>to swirl about a violent clash</i>

446
01:04:38,172 --> 01:04:42,030
<i>between forces of the US military</i>
<i>and an unknown adversary</i>

447
01:04:42,135 --> 01:04:45,052
<i>on the campus of Culver University</i>
<i>earlier today.</i>

448
01:04:45,157 --> 01:04:48,389
<i>Sophomores Jack McGhee and Jim Wilson</i>
<i>witnessed some of the battle.</i>

449
01:04:48,492 --> 01:04:49,952
<i>JIM: It was so big.</i>

450
01:04:50,056 --> 01:04:52,871
<i>- It was like this huge, like, hulk!</i>
<i>- Yeah.</i>

451
01:04:52,974 --> 01:04:55,998
<i>FEMALE REPORTER: McGhee, who happens</i>
<i>to be a reporter for the campus paper,</i>

452
01:04:56,101 --> 01:04:57,769
<i>captured this on his cell phone.</i>

453
01:04:57,873 --> 01:04:59,541
<i>Further search for the mysterious "hulk"</i>

454
01:04:59,646 --> 01:05:04,128
<i>was postponed by powerful thunderstorms</i>
<i>in the Smoky Mountain National Forest.</i>

455
01:05:11,737 --> 01:05:14,655
Not too short back there.

456
01:05:14,760 --> 01:05:17,157
I have done this before, you know.

457
01:05:33,106 --> 01:05:35,608
I don't know how you've done this
on your own for all this time.

458
01:05:35,711 --> 01:05:37,693
With clippers, usually.

459
01:05:37,797 --> 01:05:39,360
(BETTY CHUCKLING)

460
01:06:21,159 --> 01:06:22,722
(WATCH BEEPING)

461
01:06:27,309 --> 01:06:29,184
(WATCH BEEPING RAPIDLY)

462
01:06:32,519 --> 01:06:35,231
- Wait, wait, wait. Wait.
- What? What?

463
01:06:35,335 --> 01:06:36,690
We can't do this.

464
01:06:36,795 --> 01:06:38,775
- It's okay. I want to.
- No.

465
01:06:39,922 --> 01:06:40,965
No.

466
01:06:42,110 --> 01:06:43,362
I can't.

467
01:06:43,570 --> 01:06:45,134
(BEEPING SLOWS)

468
01:06:46,905 --> 01:06:48,887
I can't get too excited.

469
01:06:50,137 --> 01:06:51,597
(BEEPING STOPS)

470
01:06:51,597 --> 01:06:53,681
Not even a little excited?

471
01:06:53,784 --> 01:06:55,244
(BRUCE SIGHS)

472
01:06:56,391 --> 01:06:57,746
BETTY: It's okay.

473
01:07:02,436 --> 01:07:04,313
Sir, it's Blonsky.

474
01:07:06,813 --> 01:07:09,733
Has anyone found out
if he has next of kin or family?

475
01:07:10,567 --> 01:07:12,130
Ask him yourself.

476
01:07:15,987 --> 01:07:17,030
Sir?

477
01:07:37,251 --> 01:07:41,213
- Good to see you back on your feet, soldier.
- Thank you, sir.

478
01:07:48,197 --> 01:07:49,447
How do you feel?

479
01:07:51,427 --> 01:07:53,824
Pissed off and ready for round three.

480
01:08:00,288 --> 01:08:04,250
Basically, we can't use any of this,
because they can track all of it.

481
01:08:04,353 --> 01:08:07,168
Well, my lip gloss? Can they track that?

482
01:08:08,106 --> 01:08:11,233
- No. You can take your lip gloss.
- Thank you.

483
01:08:11,338 --> 01:08:14,255
- Well, I need my glasses.
- Well, you can take

484
01:08:14,360 --> 01:08:15,507
- your glasses and your watch, okay?
- Okay.

485
01:08:15,610 --> 01:08:19,154
We can use most of it. We just can't use
the credit cards, the ID or the phone.

486
01:08:19,260 --> 01:08:21,551
- Don't even turn that on.
- Okay.

487
01:08:21,657 --> 01:08:23,845
And we'll take the cash, obviously.

488
01:08:23,948 --> 01:08:27,805
How will we get where we need to go
on $40 and no credit cards?

489
01:08:30,829 --> 01:08:33,747
Well, we could sell this.

490
01:08:33,851 --> 01:08:37,395
No. No, that's the only thing
you have left from her. No.

491
01:08:39,586 --> 01:08:42,296
Well, we'll have to try and get it back.

492
01:08:42,921 --> 01:08:44,902
SPARR: Federal is
already monitoring phones,

493
01:08:45,006 --> 01:08:47,194
plastic and Dr Ross's web accounts,

494
01:08:47,298 --> 01:08:49,488
and local PD have been placed on alert.

495
01:08:49,591 --> 01:08:52,301
They'll pop up somewhere
and when they do, it comes straight to us.

496
01:08:52,407 --> 01:08:54,283
GENERAL: They're not gonna just pop up.

497
01:08:54,386 --> 01:08:57,411
He made it five years and got across borders
without making any mistakes.

498
01:08:57,515 --> 01:08:59,390
He's not gonna use a damn credit card now.

499
01:08:59,807 --> 01:09:01,579
<i>If he was trying to escape,</i>
<i>he'd be long gone.</i>

500
01:09:01,684 --> 01:09:02,831
<i>He's not trying to escape this time.</i>

501
01:09:02,934 --> 01:09:05,332
<i>He's looking for help</i>
<i>and that's how we're gonna get him.</i>

502
01:09:05,436 --> 01:09:07,833
<i>We know what they're after and we know</i>
<i>he's been talking to somebody.</i>

503
01:09:07,938 --> 01:09:09,814
<i>You all have copies of the correspondence.</i>

504
01:09:10,335 --> 01:09:12,315
<i>The aliases Mr Green and Mr Blue</i>

505
01:09:12,420 --> 01:09:14,503
<i>have been added to the</i>
<i>SHIELD Operations Database.</i>

506
01:09:15,546 --> 01:09:17,215
<i>If he comes up for air, we'll be waiting.</i>

507
01:09:18,569 --> 01:09:20,759
<i>If he makes a peep, we'll hear him.</i>

508
01:09:20,863 --> 01:09:23,260
<i>And when he slips up, we'll be ready.</i>

509
01:10:06,101 --> 01:10:07,248
Hey.

510
01:10:09,020 --> 01:10:10,270
Smile.

511
01:10:20,694 --> 01:10:22,363
What is it like?

512
01:10:24,238 --> 01:10:27,052
When it happens, what do you experience?

513
01:10:27,783 --> 01:10:30,389
Remember those experiments
we volunteered for at Harvard?

514
01:10:30,493 --> 01:10:32,472
Those induced hallucinations?

515
01:10:33,306 --> 01:10:36,643
It's a lot like that,
just a thousand times amplified.

516
01:10:38,520 --> 01:10:42,479
It's like someone's poured
a litre of acid into my brain.

517
01:10:42,583 --> 01:10:47,381
- Do you remember anything?
- Just fragments. Images.

518
01:10:47,900 --> 01:10:51,028
There's too much noise.
I can never derive anything out of it.

519
01:10:51,131 --> 01:10:54,676
- But then it's still you inside it.
- No. No, it's not.

520
01:10:57,179 --> 01:11:01,243
I don't know.
In the cave, I really felt like it knew me.

521
01:11:02,077 --> 01:11:03,431
Maybe your mind is in there,

522
01:11:03,536 --> 01:11:06,141
it's just overcharged
and can't process what's happening.

523
01:11:06,246 --> 01:11:09,582
I don't want to control it.
I want to get rid of it.

524
01:11:22,820 --> 01:11:24,279
Are you ready?

525
01:11:24,279 --> 01:11:26,051
Let's even the playing field a little.

526
01:11:29,490 --> 01:11:30,742
Gentlemen.

527
01:11:33,659 --> 01:11:34,597
(HORN BLARING)

528
01:11:34,703 --> 01:11:38,350
BETTY: Bruce, wake up.
There's something going on.

529
01:11:49,505 --> 01:11:52,528
We got to go. Walk toward the back.
Just don't move too fast.

530
01:12:08,060 --> 01:12:09,622
All right. Come.

531
01:12:23,485 --> 01:12:27,759
BETTY: It is a long way uptown.
I think the subway's probably quickest.

532
01:12:28,697 --> 01:12:30,573
Me in a metal tube, deep underground,

533
01:12:30,677 --> 01:12:33,074
with hundreds of people
in the most aggressive city in the world?

534
01:12:33,180 --> 01:12:35,890
Right. Let's get a cab.

535
01:12:35,993 --> 01:12:40,162
CAB DRIVER: Come on, now! Let's go!
You're too slow! You drive like a woman!

536
01:12:40,581 --> 01:12:42,872
<i>(HIP-HOP MUSIC PLAYING ON RADIO)</i>

537
01:12:45,063 --> 01:12:46,626
- Very nice. You see her?
- Oh, my.

538
01:12:46,729 --> 01:12:49,858
Very pretty. Watch out, you goat!

539
01:12:49,962 --> 01:12:51,943
Breathe, breathe, breathe.

540
01:12:55,278 --> 01:12:57,988
Are you out of your mind?

541
01:12:58,092 --> 01:12:59,344
- What is wrong with you?
- What's the matter, baby?

542
01:12:59,448 --> 01:13:01,115
You don't like a good ride?

543
01:13:01,636 --> 01:13:02,887
(GRUNTING)

544
01:13:02,992 --> 01:13:04,243
Asshole!

545
01:13:05,493 --> 01:13:06,953
(BETTY GRUNTS)

546
01:13:07,369 --> 01:13:09,872
You know, I know a few
techniques could help you

547
01:13:09,975 --> 01:13:14,145
- manage that anger very effectively.
- You zip it. We're walking.

548
01:13:14,561 --> 01:13:15,604
Okay.

549
01:13:23,213 --> 01:13:25,090
Excuse me. Dr Sterns?

550
01:13:25,194 --> 01:13:27,800
- Yes.
- I'm sorry to bother you. I'm Elizabeth Ross.

551
01:13:28,738 --> 01:13:30,717
Oh! Dr Ross!

552
01:13:30,823 --> 01:13:33,636
- I have someone who'd like to meet you.
- Okay.

553
01:13:36,243 --> 01:13:37,702
It's Mr Blue, isn't it?

554
01:13:39,474 --> 01:13:40,828
Mr Green?

555
01:13:43,122 --> 01:13:46,770
I got to tell you,
I've been wondering if you were even real.

556
01:13:46,875 --> 01:13:48,646
And if you were, what would it look like?

557
01:13:48,751 --> 01:13:53,338
A person with that much
power lurking in him.

558
01:13:53,443 --> 01:13:55,110
Nothing could have surprised me more

559
01:13:55,215 --> 01:13:58,029
than this unassuming man
shaking my hand.

560
01:13:58,132 --> 01:14:00,842
But, look. We're not strolling
into the park for a picnic, here.

561
01:14:00,842 --> 01:14:02,511
Even if everything goes perfectly,

562
01:14:02,614 --> 01:14:06,471
if we induce an episode,
if we get the dosage exactly right,

563
01:14:07,515 --> 01:14:09,390
is that going to be a lasting cure

564
01:14:09,494 --> 01:14:12,831
or just some antidote to suppress
that specific flare-up?

565
01:14:15,123 --> 01:14:16,582
I don't know.

566
01:14:17,313 --> 01:14:22,002
What I'm saying is that if we overshoot this
by even the smallest integer

567
01:14:22,940 --> 01:14:27,841
we're dealing with concentrations
with extraordinary levels of toxicity.

568
01:14:27,944 --> 01:14:32,426
- You mean it could kill him.
- Kill him? Yeah. I should say so.

569
01:14:34,198 --> 01:14:36,283
You should know that there's
a flip side to this, too.

570
01:14:36,386 --> 01:14:39,930
If we miss on the low side,
if we induce me and it fails,

571
01:14:40,036 --> 01:14:42,432
this will be very dangerous for you.

572
01:14:44,309 --> 01:14:48,375
Look. I've always been
more curious than cautious,

573
01:14:48,375 --> 01:14:52,648
and that's served me pretty well.
So, are we going to do this?

574
01:15:47,685 --> 01:15:49,353
How you feeling, man?

575
01:15:51,125 --> 01:15:52,689
Like a monster.

576
01:16:12,599 --> 01:16:14,266
Okay. On the table.

577
01:16:15,100 --> 01:16:20,416
These will protect you from yourself
if you have a strong reaction.

578
01:16:21,667 --> 01:16:24,586
You can tell me later
if you thought it was strong.

579
01:16:28,859 --> 01:16:33,237
Oh, come on! Stupid graduate students.

580
01:16:37,927 --> 01:16:38,970
Okay...

581
01:16:39,595 --> 01:16:41,054
You, you, you.

582
01:16:42,722 --> 01:16:46,162
This will be a somewhat novel sensation.

583
01:16:46,996 --> 01:16:48,768
(MACHINE STARTING UP)

584
01:16:48,872 --> 01:16:50,332
We have begun.

585
01:16:52,207 --> 01:16:55,229
The dialysis machine will mix the antidote
with your blood.

586
01:16:55,335 --> 01:16:59,712
Except the antidote will only take hold
once we've achieved a full reaction.

587
01:16:59,818 --> 01:17:00,965
Just relax.

588
01:17:01,797 --> 01:17:05,029
Okay. We are comprehensive.

589
01:17:08,261 --> 01:17:09,720
Here you go.

590
01:17:19,726 --> 01:17:21,707
All right. We set to pop?

591
01:17:24,314 --> 01:17:26,398
I'd take your hands off him.

592
01:17:41,304 --> 01:17:42,554
(GRUNTING)

593
01:17:46,203 --> 01:17:48,287
Oh, my God!

594
01:17:55,895 --> 01:17:57,148
(GRUNTING)

595
01:17:58,502 --> 01:18:00,587
(SCREAMING)

596
01:18:02,359 --> 01:18:04,444
Wait, wait! There's more! Wait!

597
01:18:15,180 --> 01:18:17,787
- Now. Okay, now!
- STERNS: Wait.

598
01:18:17,890 --> 01:18:20,497
Now, do it! Do it!

599
01:18:28,002 --> 01:18:30,503
Bruce! Bruce, look at me.

600
01:18:30,608 --> 01:18:35,090
Stay with me. The antidote, now!
Sterns, do it now!

601
01:18:36,548 --> 01:18:40,510
Bruce, look at me. Look in my eyes.
Please, look in my eyes.

602
01:18:40,614 --> 01:18:41,655
(MACHINE BEEPING)

603
01:18:41,761 --> 01:18:44,158
Oh, you've got to be kidding me!

604
01:18:53,538 --> 01:18:55,103
(HULK GROANING)

605
01:19:03,755 --> 01:19:04,902
Bruce.

606
01:19:05,006 --> 01:19:06,465
Oh, my God.

607
01:19:17,828 --> 01:19:20,746
Bruce? Bruce, can you hear me?

608
01:19:24,810 --> 01:19:25,957
Bruce?

609
01:19:26,895 --> 01:19:28,042
(GASPS)

610
01:19:34,817 --> 01:19:38,257
It's okay. You're okay. You're okay.

611
01:19:41,697 --> 01:19:43,051
You did it.

612
01:19:43,155 --> 01:19:45,867
He's fine. This is fantastic.

613
01:19:45,970 --> 01:19:47,220
BETTY: It's over.

614
01:19:48,158 --> 01:19:49,305
Hi.

615
01:19:49,618 --> 01:19:50,765
Hi.

616
01:19:59,104 --> 01:20:05,046
That was the most extraordinary thing
I have seen in my entire life!

617
01:20:05,150 --> 01:20:06,713
Okay, you know what? Stop, please.

618
01:20:06,818 --> 01:20:09,112
We need to go back and talk
about what just happened in there.

619
01:20:09,216 --> 01:20:13,073
Absolutely. Okay. The gamma pulse
came from the amygdala.

620
01:20:13,176 --> 01:20:14,845
- I think Dr Ross's primer...
- Are you okay?

621
01:20:14,948 --> 01:20:18,180
...lets the cells absorb the energy
temporarily, and then it abates.

622
01:20:18,283 --> 01:20:21,099
That's why you didn't die
of radiation sickness years ago!

623
01:20:21,203 --> 01:20:23,912
Now, maybe we've neutralised
those cells permanently,

624
01:20:24,018 --> 01:20:25,894
or maybe we just suppressed that event.

625
01:20:25,997 --> 01:20:28,291
I'm inclined to think the latter,
but it's hard to know

626
01:20:28,395 --> 01:20:30,167
because none of our
test subjects ever survived.

627
01:20:30,271 --> 01:20:31,835
- Of course, they weren't getting the primer!
- Wait, wait.

628
01:20:31,939 --> 01:20:33,398
- Wait, what did you just say?
- They weren't getting

629
01:20:33,502 --> 01:20:36,003
- the myostatin primer...
- No, no, no. Test subjects?

630
01:20:37,046 --> 01:20:38,819
What test subjects?

631
01:20:39,547 --> 01:20:40,591
Come with me.

632
01:20:57,685 --> 01:21:01,542
- SPARR: What's the activity level?
- Snipers are covering Alpha sector.

633
01:21:02,376 --> 01:21:03,835
<i>STERNS ON RADIO:</i>
<i>We started on rats and mice,</i>

634
01:21:03,939 --> 01:21:06,440
<i>but it just completely fried them,</i>
<i>so we had to go bigger.</i>

635
01:21:06,753 --> 01:21:09,881
And we still don't know which is more toxic,
the gamma or your blood.

636
01:21:09,985 --> 01:21:13,738
- What do you mean, my blood?
- Bruce, this is all you.

637
01:21:14,573 --> 01:21:18,533
You didn't send me much to work with,
so I had to concentrate it and make more.

638
01:21:18,636 --> 01:21:21,868
With a little more trial and error,
there's no end to what we can do!

639
01:21:21,974 --> 01:21:25,621
This is potentially Olympian!

640
01:21:25,725 --> 01:21:29,269
This gamma technology
has limitless applications.

641
01:21:29,373 --> 01:21:31,354
We'll unlock hundreds of cures.

642
01:21:31,458 --> 01:21:34,585
We will make humans
impervious to disease!

643
01:21:48,761 --> 01:21:50,429
No, no, we've got to destroy it.

644
01:21:50,951 --> 01:21:52,722
- Wait, what?
- All of it.

645
01:21:52,930 --> 01:21:54,286
Tonight. We're gonna incinerate it.

646
01:21:54,390 --> 01:21:56,578
- Is this the whole supply?
- What...

647
01:21:56,682 --> 01:21:58,247
We could get the Nobel for this!

648
01:21:58,350 --> 01:22:00,539
You don't understand
the power of this thing.

649
01:22:00,645 --> 01:22:03,250
It is too dangerous. It cannot be controlled.

650
01:22:03,875 --> 01:22:05,439
At your discretion, shooter.

651
01:22:05,542 --> 01:22:07,002
<i>STERNS ON RADIO: three of us!</i>
<i>This is Promethean fire!</i>

652
01:22:07,002 --> 01:22:08,046
<i>BRUCE ON RADIO: It's just...</i>

653
01:22:08,149 --> 01:22:09,399
<i>SOLDIER ON RADIO: No shot.</i>

654
01:22:12,735 --> 01:22:14,507
Blonsky's going in.

655
01:22:16,801 --> 01:22:19,615
<i>GENERAL: Blonsky, stand down.</i>
<i>My daughter's in there!</i>

656
01:22:22,222 --> 01:22:23,264
We have the antidote now.

657
01:22:23,368 --> 01:22:26,182
They don't want the antidote!
They want to make it a weapon!

658
01:22:28,268 --> 01:22:29,935
(SIRENS WAILING)

659
01:22:33,061 --> 01:22:35,042
And if we let it go, we will never get it back.

660
01:22:35,355 --> 01:22:37,336
<i>You don't know how powerful this thing is.</i>

661
01:22:37,439 --> 01:22:39,421
I hate the government
just as much as anyone,

662
01:22:39,524 --> 01:22:41,296
but you're being a little paranoid,
don't you think?

663
01:22:45,257 --> 01:22:46,404
(GASPS)

664
01:22:49,114 --> 01:22:50,573
Bruce! Bruce!

665
01:22:52,345 --> 01:22:53,596
Get out.

666
01:22:54,430 --> 01:22:55,890
(BETTY SCREAMS)

667
01:22:56,828 --> 01:22:59,537
Where is it? Come on, where is it?

668
01:23:00,060 --> 01:23:01,310
(BRUCE EXCLAIMS)

669
01:23:01,413 --> 01:23:03,289
(WATCH BEEPING RAPIDLY)

670
01:23:03,811 --> 01:23:05,479
Show him to me.

671
01:23:06,939 --> 01:23:08,189
Blonsky!

672
01:23:08,398 --> 01:23:10,274
(HEART BEATING SLOWLY)

673
01:23:16,738 --> 01:23:17,779
SOLDIER: Miss!

674
01:23:19,344 --> 01:23:20,698
Take this.

675
01:23:24,346 --> 01:23:28,828
If you took it from me, I'm gonna
put you in a hole for the rest of your life.

676
01:23:34,667 --> 01:23:35,814
Betty.

677
01:23:37,792 --> 01:23:40,712
I will never forgive what you've done to him.

678
01:23:40,815 --> 01:23:42,171
He's a fugitive.

679
01:23:42,274 --> 01:23:44,256
You made him a fugitive

680
01:23:44,359 --> 01:23:47,800
to cover your failures
and to protect your career.

681
01:23:48,634 --> 01:23:51,448
Don't ever speak to me
as your daughter again.

682
01:23:53,740 --> 01:23:57,180
It's only because you're my daughter
that you're not in handcuffs, too.

683
01:24:02,079 --> 01:24:03,331
SPARR: Are you telling me
you can make more like him?

684
01:24:03,435 --> 01:24:08,126
No! Not yet. I sorted out a few pieces,
but it's not like I can put together

685
01:24:08,229 --> 01:24:11,564
the same Humpty Dumpty,
if that's what you're asking.

686
01:24:11,670 --> 01:24:15,528
He was a freak accident!
The goal is to do it better!

687
01:24:15,631 --> 01:24:17,507
So Banner's the only...

688
01:24:21,364 --> 01:24:25,742
- She's an annoying bitch.
- Why are you always hitting people?

689
01:24:28,140 --> 01:24:33,247
Now what possibly could I have done
to deserve such aggression?

690
01:24:33,351 --> 01:24:36,061
It's not what you've done.
It's what you're gonna do.

691
01:24:37,000 --> 01:24:39,502
I want what you got out of Banner.
I want that.

692
01:24:42,942 --> 01:24:47,006
You look like you've got a little
something in you already, don't you?

693
01:24:48,362 --> 01:24:52,010
I want more.
You've seen what he becomes, right?

694
01:24:52,739 --> 01:24:53,886
I have.

695
01:24:54,823 --> 01:24:56,387
And it's beautiful.

696
01:24:57,221 --> 01:24:58,471
Godlike.

697
01:24:58,680 --> 01:25:00,349
Well, I want that.

698
01:25:02,537 --> 01:25:04,622
I need that. Make me that.

699
01:25:05,560 --> 01:25:08,479
I don't know what you've got
inside you already.

700
01:25:08,582 --> 01:25:10,146
The mix could be

701
01:25:10,876 --> 01:25:12,336
an abomination.

702
01:25:16,087 --> 01:25:18,903
(GASPING) I didn't say I was unwilling.

703
01:25:19,425 --> 01:25:23,176
I just need informed consent.

704
01:25:25,679 --> 01:25:27,451
And you've given it.

705
01:26:08,623 --> 01:26:12,792
This is what I was trying to explain.

706
01:26:12,896 --> 01:26:17,796
I don't know what you've been
ladling into yourself.

707
01:26:17,900 --> 01:26:19,985
But clearly it worked.

708
01:26:20,090 --> 01:26:23,738
Let's assume you don't understand
a word I'm saying,

709
01:26:23,842 --> 01:26:28,636
but if you'll just get back on the table,

710
01:26:28,742 --> 01:26:31,243
I can fix this.

711
01:26:31,346 --> 01:26:33,118
(ABOMINATION GROWLING)

712
01:26:36,560 --> 01:26:38,435
(ABOMINATION LAUGHING)

713
01:26:46,149 --> 01:26:47,817
SOLDIER 1 : Shoot it!
SOLDIER 2 : Hey!

714
01:26:48,650 --> 01:26:49,693
No!

715
01:26:55,529 --> 01:26:57,301
(SOLDIERS SCREAMING)

716
01:26:59,283 --> 01:27:01,264
SOLDIER 5 : Delta 4 to Leader.

717
01:27:01,368 --> 01:27:03,140
They took out two of our guys,
two of our guys!

718
01:27:03,243 --> 01:27:05,953
Blonsky and the Major are still inside!

719
01:27:07,725 --> 01:27:08,768
(ABOMINATION GROWLING)

720
01:27:08,872 --> 01:27:11,061
Come on! Move, move, move, move!

721
01:27:19,087 --> 01:27:20,650
It's over there!

722
01:27:22,423 --> 01:27:23,570
SOLDIER 2 : Drop them!

723
01:27:23,673 --> 01:27:25,967
SOLDIER 3 : What is that thing?
SOLDIER 4 : Shoot it!

724
01:27:27,323 --> 01:27:28,886
(WOMAN SCREAMING)

725
01:27:35,453 --> 01:27:39,206
Okay. All right! You... You, drive!
Let's go! Move, move!

726
01:27:39,310 --> 01:27:40,664
SOLDIER 5 : Delta 4 to Leader!
SOLDIER 6 : Go, go, go, go, go!

727
01:27:40,769 --> 01:27:42,645
SOLDIER 5 : Something big
just went off down here!

728
01:27:43,166 --> 01:27:45,251
General, you should hear this!

729
01:27:45,355 --> 01:27:48,274
The Hulk is in the street!
I repeat, the Hulk is in the street!

730
01:27:50,880 --> 01:27:52,965
That's impossible.
You get a hold of yourself, young man.

731
01:27:53,069 --> 01:27:54,944
You get it together. What is your position?

732
01:27:55,257 --> 01:27:58,385
121 st Street, heading north on Broadway!

733
01:27:58,488 --> 01:27:59,948
Turn us around.

734
01:28:06,932 --> 01:28:10,163
We're going back. Why are we going back?

735
01:28:10,268 --> 01:28:11,831
Damn it! Give me eyes down there!

736
01:28:12,248 --> 01:28:13,603
Yes, sir!

737
01:28:15,583 --> 01:28:17,460
<i>What the hell was that?</i>

738
01:28:17,877 --> 01:28:19,439
Go, go, go!

739
01:28:35,077 --> 01:28:36,744
(SIRENS WAILING)

740
01:28:42,998 --> 01:28:44,248
No!

741
01:28:49,564 --> 01:28:51,128
(WOMAN SCREAMING)

742
01:28:53,838 --> 01:28:55,090
(GROWLING)

743
01:29:00,510 --> 01:29:01,865
One of yours?

744
01:29:02,073 --> 01:29:05,201
Oh, my God. What have you done?

745
01:29:07,493 --> 01:29:09,369
OFFICER: Fire at him, fire at him!

746
01:29:13,747 --> 01:29:15,729
Do you think a rifle's gonna hurt that?

747
01:29:16,248 --> 01:29:17,395
Come on!

748
01:29:20,939 --> 01:29:22,087
Sweet.

749
01:29:22,608 --> 01:29:24,380
(ABOMINATION ROARING)

750
01:29:25,005 --> 01:29:26,256
Booyah!

751
01:29:31,363 --> 01:29:32,720
(LAUGHING)

752
01:29:41,057 --> 01:29:42,829
(CAR ALARMS BEEPING)

753
01:29:44,289 --> 01:29:45,539
Get out of there, soldier!

754
01:29:48,979 --> 01:29:50,543
Stacy!

755
01:30:21,189 --> 01:30:23,064
Give me a real fight!

756
01:30:31,197 --> 01:30:32,344
Sir?

757
01:30:35,052 --> 01:30:36,199
Sir?

758
01:30:37,762 --> 01:30:40,681
Tell them to bring everything they've got
and head for Harlem.

759
01:30:44,122 --> 01:30:47,560
It has to be me.
You have to take me back there.

760
01:30:47,873 --> 01:30:49,438
What are you saying?

761
01:30:49,645 --> 01:30:50,898
You think you can control it?

762
01:30:51,001 --> 01:30:54,127
No, no, not control it,
but, I don't know, maybe aim it.

763
01:30:54,233 --> 01:30:55,692
And what if you can't?

764
01:30:57,152 --> 01:30:58,923
We made this thing.

765
01:30:59,444 --> 01:31:00,798
All of us.

766
01:31:01,737 --> 01:31:02,988
Please.

767
01:31:07,990 --> 01:31:10,389
- Land us near it.
- No, no. No, keep us high.

768
01:31:12,056 --> 01:31:13,306
Open the back door.

769
01:31:19,145 --> 01:31:23,939
Bruce! Bruce, stop!
Stop! What are you doing?

770
01:31:24,043 --> 01:31:27,796
Think about this!
You don't even know if you'll change!

771
01:31:29,777 --> 01:31:33,009
You don't have to do this!
Please, this is insane!

772
01:31:33,113 --> 01:31:34,780
Betty, I've got to try.

773
01:31:36,970 --> 01:31:38,324
I'm sorry.

774
01:32:00,944 --> 01:32:02,612
Oh, shooot!

775
01:32:06,676 --> 01:32:09,490
- Get her in here!
- Come on, miss.

776
01:32:25,126 --> 01:32:26,793
(HULK GROWLING)

777
01:32:26,898 --> 01:32:28,983
There. Betty!

778
01:32:30,130 --> 01:32:31,694
(PEOPLE CLAMOURING)

779
01:32:43,784 --> 01:32:45,037
(ROARING)

780
01:32:48,059 --> 01:32:49,519
Hulk!

781
01:32:54,313 --> 01:32:56,085
Yeah!

782
01:33:06,301 --> 01:33:07,863
(BOTH GROWLING)

783
01:33:37,885 --> 01:33:39,761
(ABOMINATION LAUGHING)

784
01:33:40,282 --> 01:33:41,533
Come on!

785
01:33:42,470 --> 01:33:45,077
<i>(INDISTINCT CHATTERING</i>
<i>ON POLICE RADIO)</i>

786
01:33:56,542 --> 01:33:57,793
(ROARING)

787
01:34:13,742 --> 01:34:15,721
Is that all you've got?

788
01:34:29,480 --> 01:34:32,190
Use that thing, soldier! Give him some help!

789
01:34:32,296 --> 01:34:33,546
Which one?

790
01:34:33,649 --> 01:34:35,944
Help the green one, damn it!
Which one do you think?

791
01:34:36,047 --> 01:34:37,923
Cut the other one in half!

792
01:34:40,635 --> 01:34:41,782
Ross!

793
01:35:06,484 --> 01:35:08,256
Keep it on him!

794
01:35:22,016 --> 01:35:24,310
(HULK AND ABOMINATION GRUNTING)

795
01:35:36,505 --> 01:35:39,423
PILOT: Look, I got to put it down!
GENERAL: Hang on!

796
01:35:39,528 --> 01:35:41,091
(ALARM SOUNDING)

797
01:35:49,639 --> 01:35:51,932
(ABOMINATION AND HULK GRUNTING)

798
01:36:46,657 --> 01:36:47,804
Dad?

799
01:36:48,117 --> 01:36:49,471
(GROANING)

800
01:36:50,409 --> 01:36:52,911
Are you hurt? Let me help you.

801
01:37:00,729 --> 01:37:02,501
I'm all right. Just find a way out.

802
01:37:04,899 --> 01:37:06,149
(GROWLING)

803
01:37:15,530 --> 01:37:16,989
(CHUCKLING)

804
01:37:50,345 --> 01:37:57,016
You don't deserve this power!
Now watch her die!

805
01:38:14,215 --> 01:38:15,675
(BOTH GRUNTING)

806
01:38:47,779 --> 01:38:49,448
Look out!

807
01:39:20,198 --> 01:39:21,448
General?

808
01:39:27,702 --> 01:39:30,309
Any last words?

809
01:39:33,122 --> 01:39:36,561
Hulk smash!

810
01:40:22,113 --> 01:40:23,990
(ROARING)

811
01:40:24,095 --> 01:40:25,658
BETTY: Stop!

812
01:40:55,886 --> 01:40:57,139
(ROARING)

813
01:41:46,337 --> 01:41:47,692
It's okay.

814
01:41:57,804 --> 01:41:59,471
Betty.

815
01:42:08,539 --> 01:42:09,791
(GROWLING)

816
01:42:45,023 --> 01:42:46,689
(SEAGULLS SQUAWKING)

817
01:44:01,533 --> 01:44:03,096
(HEART BEATING)

818
01:44:08,307 --> 01:44:10,185
(HEART BEATING RAPIDLY)

819
01:44:27,487 --> 01:44:28,842
GENERAL: Reload.

820
01:44:36,346 --> 01:44:37,599
Reload.

821
01:44:53,546 --> 01:44:56,777
TONY: The smell of stale beer and defeat.

822
01:44:56,881 --> 01:44:58,548
You know, I hate to say,
"I told you so," General,

823
01:44:58,654 --> 01:45:03,033
but that Super Soldier programme
was put on ice for a reason.

824
01:45:03,136 --> 01:45:06,055
I've always felt hardware was more reliable.

825
01:45:06,264 --> 01:45:08,556
- Stark.
- General.

826
01:45:10,850 --> 01:45:13,351
You always wear such nice suits.

827
01:45:14,394 --> 01:45:15,645
TouchE

828
01:45:16,582 --> 01:45:20,336
- I hear you have an unusual problem.
- You should talk.

829
01:45:20,439 --> 01:45:21,899
You should listen.

830
01:45:24,609 --> 01:45:28,048
What if I told you
we were putting a team together?

